11
00:03:55,451 --> 00:03:57,527
我想……
l think. . . .

12
00:03:59,372 --> 00:04:01,910
我给你找着了一个
l think l found you one.

13
00:04:04,961 --> 00:04:08,496
这次我可是给你打电话了
Look, l called you, right?

14
00:04:09,340 --> 00:04:14,880
我一发现自己搞不定
就马上给你打电话了，约翰
Soon as l couldn't pull it out myself,
l called you, John.

15
00:04:28,943 --> 00:04:32,893
别担心，没事的
我们必须得把她绑上，你明白吗？
lt's okay, it's okay.
We had to tie her down, okay?

16
00:04:33,239 --> 00:04:34,947
没事的
lt's okay.

17
00:05:28,127 --> 00:05:30,832
我是康斯坦丁
This is Constantine.

18
00:05:31,005 --> 00:05:36,130
约翰・康斯坦丁
你这混蛋
John Constantine, asshole.

19
00:05:43,643 --> 00:05:45,635
当然
Sure.

20
00:06:08,001 --> 00:06:09,827
怎么了？
What the hell?

21
00:06:27,478 --> 00:06:28,807
我需要一面镜子
l need a mirror.

22
00:06:28,980 --> 00:06:32,100
快去拿！
至少要3英尺高
Now. At least 3 feet high.

23
00:06:32,275 --> 00:06:34,944
愣着干嘛，快去拿啊！
Move! Go, now!

24
00:06:48,875 --> 00:06:50,832
我是克雷默
This is Kramer.

25
00:06:51,419 --> 00:06:54,373
查斯・克雷默
你这混蛋
Chas Kramer, asshole.

26
00:06:54,547 --> 00:06:56,255
混蛋
Asshole.

27
00:06:56,424 --> 00:07:01,631
什么？哦，我是克雷默
查斯・克雷默，混蛋
What? Oh, this is Kramer.
Chas Kramer, asshole.

28
00:07:01,804 --> 00:07:03,927
- 查斯！
- 什么事？
-Chas!
-What?

29
00:07:04,098 --> 00:07:06,850
- 把车挪开
- 为什么？
-Move the car.
-Why?

30
00:07:07,685 --> 00:07:09,808
叫你挪你就挪！
Move the damn car!

31
00:07:12,857 --> 00:07:14,232
“查斯，把车挪开”
''Chas, move the car. ''

32
00:07:16,444 --> 00:07:17,772
好吧，挪了
There, car's moved.

33
00:07:28,915 --> 00:07:30,907
把镜子举起来，对着床
Lift it up over the bed.

34
00:07:32,835 --> 00:07:36,999
把那头系牢
亨内斯，从上面拉过去
Tie that end off.
Hennessy, over the top.

35
00:07:38,341 --> 00:07:43,680
把你们的眼睛闭上
不管发生什么都别睁开
Close your eyes.
And whatever happens, don't look.

36
00:07:55,733 --> 00:07:57,726
不！
No!

37
00:08:03,825 --> 00:08:06,113
现身吧
Show yourself.

38
00:08:10,123 --> 00:08:12,246
来笑一个，你这傻X
Smile pretty, you vain prick.

39
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:23,125
操你妈！
For your boss.

40
00:08:23,761 --> 00:08:25,220
拉！
Pull it!

41
00:08:51,706 --> 00:08:53,615
妈妈？
Ma? Ma?

42
00:09:29,827 --> 00:09:33,991
我说得没错吧，约翰，给你找着一个
是不是？
Like l said, l found you something,
didn't l, John? Didn't l?

43
00:09:34,207 --> 00:09:35,831
那儿怎么了？
What happened in there?

44
00:09:43,466 --> 00:09:45,506
最近会议很多吧
Going to a lot of meetings, l see.

45
00:09:45,677 --> 00:09:47,799
闹得我都睡不着
Keeps the voices out so l can sleep.

46
00:09:49,389 --> 00:09:51,428
我得睡觉，约翰
l have to sleep, John.

47
00:09:51,933 --> 00:09:54,638
我需要帮助，神父
l need some help, Father.

48
00:09:55,395 --> 00:09:56,937
你？
You do?

49
00:09:57,313 --> 00:09:58,855
要我帮助？
From me?

50
00:09:59,023 --> 00:10:00,731
什么样的……？
What kind of--?

51
00:10:03,069 --> 00:10:07,149
- 听着，我……
- 你那种驱魔术不对
-Hey, listen, l--
-That exorcism wasn't right.

52
00:10:10,326 --> 00:10:11,986
听着广播
Listen to the ether.

53
00:10:13,079 --> 00:10:16,578
如果有什么异常，一定要告诉我
Anything unusual, you let me know.

54
00:10:17,208 --> 00:10:22,119
来吧，你不需要它的保护
它今天可能还会回来
Come on, you don't need its protection.
lt'll be like back in the day.

55
00:10:25,425 --> 00:10:27,501
或许几天
A few days.

56
00:10:27,677 --> 00:10:29,005
好吧
Okay.

57
00:10:29,178 --> 00:10:32,594
好吧，为了你，约翰
Okay. For you, John.

58
00:10:36,102 --> 00:10:39,553
约翰，你明知这不是我的车
John, why would you do that
if you know it's not my car?

59
00:10:39,772 --> 00:10:42,310
- 我告诉过你让你挪开的
- 你是告诉过我
-l told you to move it.
-You did tell me to move it. . .

60
00:10:42,483 --> 00:10:45,983
可是如果你告诉我
你要扔下来一个装着魔鬼的300磅的镜子
. . .but if you'd said you were dropping
a 300-pound mirror with a demon. . .

61
00:10:46,154 --> 00:10:47,981
我会把车挪得更远一点
. . .l would've moved it further, John.

62
00:10:48,364 --> 00:10:51,816
- 去阿尔瓦拉多大街
- 好的先生，我知道怎么走
-Take Alvarado.
-Yeah, thank you. l know what to take.

63
00:10:53,161 --> 00:10:56,861
你有没有考虑过，如果多告诉我一些事情
说不定我能帮上忙呢？
You ever think if you told me more now
that maybe l could help out?

64
00:10:57,040 --> 00:10:58,368
- 没有？
- 没有
-No?
-Nope.

65
00:10:58,541 --> 00:10:59,869
没有？
Nope?

66
00:11:00,043 --> 00:11:02,119
当然是――没有
Of course it's a nope.

67
00:11:39,082 --> 00:11:40,790
保佑我，神父，我有罪
Bless me, Father, for l have sinned.

68
00:11:44,337 --> 00:11:46,045
我已经……
It's been...

69
00:11:47,256 --> 00:11:50,257
有两个礼拜没来忏悔了
... two weeks since my last confession.

70
00:11:53,513 --> 00:11:55,801
今天我杀了个人
l killed a man today.

71
00:11:56,849 --> 00:11:58,593
又一个
Another one.

72
00:12:03,189 --> 00:12:08,017
我甚至连他长什么样都没看清
l didn't even see his face, l just. . .

73
00:12:09,028 --> 00:12:11,436
就扣下了扳机
接着他就死了
. . .pulled the trigger, and he went away.

74
00:12:12,657 --> 00:12:18,826
大多数警察20年都不开一枪
Most cops go 20 years
without firing their guns.

75
00:12:20,081 --> 00:12:24,079
而我却总是知道
这些家伙藏在哪儿
Why do I always know
where these guys are?

76
00:12:24,252 --> 00:12:27,585
该朝哪儿瞄准，什么时候开枪
Where to aim, when to fire.

77
00:12:29,215 --> 00:12:32,169
神父，我在想
会不会是我有什么问题？
I'm wondering, is there
something wrong with me, Father?

78
00:12:33,344 --> 00:12:35,004
被诅咒了？
Something damned?

79
00:12:35,179 --> 00:12:40,518
上帝自有安排
他给我们每个人都安排好了
God has a plan for you.
He has a plan for us all.

80
00:12:40,852 --> 00:12:45,099
别让罪恶吞没了你的信念
You mustn 't let your faith
be overshadowed by guilt.

81
00:12:45,273 --> 00:12:47,312
是的，我在努力
Yeah, I'm trying.

82
00:12:48,151 --> 00:12:50,558
一直都在努力
I'm trying real hard.

83
00:12:52,155 --> 00:12:53,483
伊莎贝尔
Isabel.

84
00:13:44,499 --> 00:13:46,705
伊莎贝尔
Isabel.

85
00:14:43,308 --> 00:14:45,633
我所战胜的东西
Things l've beaten.

86
00:14:46,019 --> 00:14:49,518
大多数人听都没听说过
Things most people never even heard of.

87
00:14:49,814 --> 00:14:53,100
可是现在呢
我却要被这玩意儿搞定
And now l'm gonna be done in by this.

88
00:14:54,235 --> 00:14:56,560
你也不是第一个了，约翰
Wouldn't be the first, John.

89
00:14:58,364 --> 00:15:00,487
得了吧，莱丝
Come on, Les.

90
00:15:00,658 --> 00:15:02,983
你救过我一次
这次也可以，对吗？
You saved me before,
you can do it again, right?

91
00:15:03,161 --> 00:15:06,031
癌细胞已经扩散了
This is aggressive.

92
00:15:07,332 --> 00:15:10,286
20年前，你不想来这儿
Twenty years ago,
you didn't wanna be here.

93
00:15:11,169 --> 00:15:13,457
现在你又不想离开
Now you don't wanna leave.

94
00:15:14,130 --> 00:15:16,288
你还抽
Yeah, that's a good idea.

95
00:15:19,260 --> 00:15:21,253
约翰，你真的需要准备一下了
John, you really need to prepare.

96
00:15:25,141 --> 00:15:28,806
- 安排后事吧
- 没必要
-Make arrangements.
-No need.

97
00:15:29,020 --> 00:15:32,140
我很清楚自己何去何从
l already know exactly where l'm going.

98
00:15:36,235 --> 00:15:38,109
- 早
- 早上好
-Morning.
-Good morning.

99
00:15:38,780 --> 00:15:41,235
- 早上好
- 探长
-Good morning.
-Detective.

100
00:15:41,407 --> 00:15:43,234
- 不，不不
- 安吉拉，等等
-No, no, no.
-Angela, wait.

101
00:15:43,409 --> 00:15:46,079
你还是别看了，好吗？别看了
You don't need to see this, okay? No.

102
00:15:47,205 --> 00:15:48,747
大家先回避一下
Give us the room, please.

103
00:16:19,946 --> 00:16:22,022
伊莎贝尔
lsabel.

104
00:16:28,746 --> 00:16:31,035
她从屋顶上掉下来的？
She fell from the roof?

105
00:16:31,207 --> 00:16:33,034
她跳下来的
She jumped.

106
00:16:35,253 --> 00:16:36,795
- 不可能
- 听着
-No.
-Look. . .

107
00:16:36,963 --> 00:16:41,126
我知道这很难接受
可她有病
. . .l know it's hard to accept.
She was sick.

108
00:16:49,642 --> 00:16:53,177
- 伊莎贝尔不会自杀的
- 安吉
-lsabel wouldn't kill herself.
-Angie.

109
00:16:53,813 --> 00:16:55,889
- 她不会自杀的
- 探长
-She wouldn't kill herself.
-Detective.

110
00:16:56,065 --> 00:16:57,394
- 皮瑞尔德
- 探长
-Period.
-Detective.

111
00:16:57,567 --> 00:16:59,191
皮瑞尔德！
Period!

112
00:16:59,986 --> 00:17:03,936
安吉，监控录像都拍下来了
Angie, there were security cameras.

113
00:17:13,499 --> 00:17:16,749
- 等一下，是下去么？
- 如果我有办法，当然不想“下去”
-Hold the door. You going down?
-Not if l can help it.

114
00:18:07,470 --> 00:18:09,048
有新案子？
A new case?

115
00:18:09,555 --> 00:18:14,976
什么大案子？
是你期待已久的吗？
The big score? The mother lode?
The one you've been waiting for?

116
00:18:15,228 --> 00:18:18,182
- 少奉承我
- 习惯了
-Humor me.
-Don't l always?

117
00:18:23,236 --> 00:18:26,771
哦，这是……
太感激了，谢谢
Oh, yeah, that's--
Much obliged. Thank you.

118
00:18:28,741 --> 00:18:30,485
最近还好吗，约翰？
How you feeling, John?

119
00:18:30,743 --> 00:18:32,321
看看有什么新的货色
So, what's new?

120
00:18:36,624 --> 00:18:40,373
教皇遇刺时留下的子弹碎屑
Bullet shavings from
the assassination attempt on the pope. . .

121
00:18:40,545 --> 00:18:44,163
采自约旦河的圣水针剂
. . .holy-water ampoules
from the River Jordan. . .

122
00:18:44,340 --> 00:18:49,251
还有……哦，这个你肯定喜欢
从阿米蒂维勒村找来的尖叫甲虫
（译者注：参考电影"The Amityville Horror"）
. . .and-- Oh, you'll love this.
--screech beetle from Amityville.

123
00:18:51,597 --> 00:18:55,512
是啊，对你来说很有趣
可对“下面”的东西来说，这就像黑板上钉钉
Yeah, it's funny to you, but to the
fallen, that's like nails on a chalkboard.

124
00:18:55,685 --> 00:18:58,805
你和虫子，到底是什么关系？
What is it, exactly, with you and bugs?

125
00:18:59,564 --> 00:19:01,889
我只是喜欢它们
l just like them.

126
00:19:02,066 --> 00:19:03,940
是啊，谁不喜欢？
Yeah. Who doesn't?

127
00:19:06,112 --> 00:19:08,152
悠着点，大英雄
Yeah, easy there, hero.

128
00:19:08,323 --> 00:19:11,905
- 这是“龙之息”
- 我还以为你再也搞不到了呢
-That's dragon's breath.
-l thought you couldn't get it anymore.

129
00:19:12,076 --> 00:19:16,869
是这样，我朋友的朋友……
Yeah, well, l know a guy
who knows a guy.

130
00:19:23,046 --> 00:19:26,628
好吧，这次是什么行动？
So, what's the action?

131
00:19:27,175 --> 00:19:30,875
我刚把一个魔兵
从一个小女孩的身体里赶出来
l just pulled a soldier demon
out of a little girl.

132
00:19:31,304 --> 00:19:34,139
看起来好像它想要复活
Looked like it was trying
to come through.

133
00:19:35,850 --> 00:19:37,178
我懂你的意思
Yeah, l know how it sounds.

134
00:19:37,352 --> 00:19:39,640
可是约翰，我们对他们来说
只不过是掌中的玩偶
No, we're finger puppets
to them, John. . .

135
00:19:39,812 --> 00:19:41,188
而不是某种入口
. . .not doorways.

136
00:19:41,356 --> 00:19:45,436
他们可以操纵我们
但不能穿透结界进到我们的世界中
They can work us, but they can't
come through onto our plane.

137
00:19:45,610 --> 00:19:48,231
还是查一下卷轴吧
看看以前有没有先例
Check the scrolls anyway.
See if there's any precedent.

138
00:19:48,404 --> 00:19:50,313
没问题，约翰
Sure thing, John.

139
00:19:51,407 --> 00:19:53,067
还有什么事吗？
Anything else?

140
00:19:53,242 --> 00:19:56,279
你那里有没有什么可以……？
Wouldn't happen to have
anything for a--?

141
00:19:57,955 --> 00:19:59,284
免费的
（译者注：止咳药）
On the house.

142
00:20:00,041 --> 00:20:03,825
好吧，我有个问题
我还得做你的奴隶到几时？
All right, question. How much longer
do l have to be your slave, John?

143
00:20:05,713 --> 00:20:07,920
你不是我的奴隶，查斯
You're not my slave, Chas.

144
00:20:08,758 --> 00:20:11,794
你是我非常赏识的徒弟
You're my very appreciated apprentice.

145
00:20:11,970 --> 00:20:14,128
就像汤托和罗宾一样
Like Tonto or Robin.

146
00:20:14,597 --> 00:20:17,005
还有那个胖哥身边的小家伙
Or that skinny fellow
with the fat friend.

147
00:20:17,183 --> 00:20:21,050
好吧，那我除了开车之外
就不能干点别的了么？
Right. So then why don't l apprentice
something besides driving, then, John?

148
00:20:23,940 --> 00:20:25,648
约翰？约翰
John? John.

149
00:20:26,901 --> 00:20:29,570
很高兴和你谈话，约翰
l love our little talks, John.

150
00:20:43,167 --> 00:20:44,994
您的外套，康斯坦丁先生
May l take your coat, Mr. Constantine?

151
00:20:45,169 --> 00:20:47,957
不用了，谢谢
我一会儿就走
No, thanks,
l'm not gonna be staying long.

152
00:20:48,131 --> 00:20:52,709
- 这位女士，您呢？
- 哦不用了，我也一会儿就走
-How about you, ma'am?
-Oh, no, l'm not staying long either.

153
00:20:53,094 --> 00:20:55,383
我真的要和他说话
有重要的事
l really need to speak with him.
lt's important.

154
00:20:55,555 --> 00:20:58,260
先到先得
First come, first served.

155
00:21:01,477 --> 00:21:04,514
看来你到哪儿都是这么粗鲁
So you're rude no matter where you are.

156
00:21:13,239 --> 00:21:15,113
- 神父
- 你好
-Father.
-Hi.

157
00:21:16,159 --> 00:21:19,409
- 带来什么新消息了
- 是的，刚和主教谈过
-You have news. Yes.
-Yes, l spoke with the bishop.

158
00:21:25,460 --> 00:21:28,081
我知道你要什么，孩子
l know what you want, son.

159
00:21:28,254 --> 00:21:31,789
你那双无所不见的眼睛还盯着我呢
加百列？
（译者注：替上帝把好消息报告世人的天使）
Still keeping your all-seeing eye
on me, Gabriel?

160
00:21:33,301 --> 00:21:35,377
承蒙夸奖
l'm flattered.

161
00:21:36,596 --> 00:21:38,802
我可以告诉你一些
Well, l could offer something. . .

162
00:21:38,973 --> 00:21:43,220
关于牧羊人是怎样
带领他最不听话的羊群的故事
. . .about how a shepherd leads
even the most wayward of his flock. . .

163
00:21:43,561 --> 00:21:45,470
可这听起来也许不够真诚
. . .but it might sound disingenuous.

164
00:21:45,647 --> 00:21:48,398
她应该得到天主教的葬礼
神父，求你了
She has to have a Catholic funeral,
Father. She has to.

165
00:21:48,566 --> 00:21:52,778
- 安杰拉，她犯的是不可饶恕的大罪
- 她不是自杀的
-Angela, it's still considered a mortal sin.
-She didn't commit suicide.

166
00:21:52,945 --> 00:21:55,567
可主教不这么想
你知道教规的
The bishop believes otherwise.
You know the rules.

167
00:21:55,740 --> 00:21:57,816
哦，教规
