00:37:07,443 --> 00:37:10,230
她的灵魂会直接下地狱
Her soul would go straight to hell. . .

330
00:37:10,405 --> 00:37:15,530
在尖叫中一次又一次地被撕裂
饱受折磨，极度痛苦
. . .where she'd be ripped apart over
and over in screaming, brutal agony. . .

331
00:37:15,702 --> 00:37:18,952
永世不得翻身，对吗？
. . .for all eternity. That it?

332
00:37:19,122 --> 00:37:21,161
我说得没错吧？
That about right?

333
00:37:28,131 --> 00:37:30,254
你他妈的
Goddamn you.

334
00:38:00,580 --> 00:38:02,074
侦探
Detective.

335
00:38:02,248 --> 00:38:05,083
如果我告诉你
上帝和魔鬼打了个赌……
What if l told you that God
and the devil made a wager. . .

336
00:38:05,251 --> 00:38:08,750
他们的赌注就是所有人类的灵魂
你信么？
. . .a kind of standing bet
for the souls of all mankind?

337
00:38:08,921 --> 00:38:11,412
我会告诉你回去找你的医生
l'd tell you to stay on your meds.

338
00:38:11,591 --> 00:38:15,885
别跟我争
他们的约定是不能直接涉足人间
Humor me. No direct contact with
humans. That would be the rule.

339
00:38:16,220 --> 00:38:20,432
- 只能施加影响，最后看谁能赢
- 好吧，我不跟你争
-Just influence. See who would win.
-Okay, l'm humoring you.

340
00:38:20,600 --> 00:38:22,676
- 可是为什么呢？
- 谁知道呢
-Why?
-Who knows.

341
00:38:22,852 --> 00:38:25,936
- 也许只是为了好玩
- 哦，这可真好玩
-Maybe just for the fun of it. No telling.
-Oh, so it's fun.

342
00:38:26,105 --> 00:38:31,100
丈夫打死妻子好玩么？
母亲淹死孩子好玩么？
lt's fun when a man beats his wife to
death, when a mother drowns her baby.

343
00:38:31,277 --> 00:38:35,026
你觉得这都归因于魔鬼？
And you think the devil is responsible?

344
00:38:35,198 --> 00:38:37,949
你错了，康斯坦丁
是人，人才是魔鬼
People are evil, Mr. Constantine. People.

345
00:38:38,117 --> 00:38:41,569
你说得很对
人性本恶
You're right. We're born
capable of terrible things.

346
00:38:41,746 --> 00:38:45,494
再加上受到其他某种东西的引导……
Then sometimes something else comes
along and gives us just the right nudge.

347
00:38:45,667 --> 00:38:49,118
好吧，谢谢你给我上了一课
Well, this has been real educational. . .

348
00:38:49,295 --> 00:38:51,003
可我不相信有什么魔鬼
. . .but l don't believe in the devil.

349
00:38:51,172 --> 00:38:54,623
你应该相信
就如魔鬼相信你的存在
You should. He believes in you.

350
00:39:14,779 --> 00:39:16,985
只是停电了
lt's a power outage.

351
00:39:17,156 --> 00:39:19,114
不像
Not likely.

352
00:39:21,744 --> 00:39:25,160
- 什么？
- 不能呆在这儿了，快走
-What?
-We should go. Now.

353
00:39:30,294 --> 00:39:32,287
那是什么？
What is that?

354
00:39:33,381 --> 00:39:35,124
翅膀
Wings.

355
00:39:35,675 --> 00:39:38,047
也许是魔爪
Maybe talons.

356
00:39:38,386 --> 00:39:41,091
别开玩笑了，你说什么？
You're kidding. Of what?

357
00:39:42,098 --> 00:39:45,099
一些不该在这儿的东西
Something that's not
supposed to be here.

358
00:39:49,022 --> 00:39:51,643
枪在这儿基本上没用
That's really not going to help.

359
00:39:56,237 --> 00:39:58,906
- 闭上眼睛
- 为什么？
-Close your eyes.
-Why?

360
00:39:59,073 --> 00:40:00,402
为了你自己
Suit yourself.

361
00:40:22,889 --> 00:40:26,055
谁说魔鬼只呆在地狱里？
Demons stay in hell, huh?

362
00:40:27,393 --> 00:40:29,469
得告诉他们
Tell them that.

363
00:40:31,606 --> 00:40:36,482
别担心
第一次都是这样
Don't worry. Happens to everyone
the first time.

364
00:40:36,736 --> 00:40:38,775
那是硫磺
lt's the sulfur.

365
00:40:39,364 --> 00:40:41,356
硫磺
Sulfur.

366
00:40:43,576 --> 00:40:45,984
那些东西是什么？
What were those things?

367
00:40:47,246 --> 00:40:49,038
魔鬼
Demons.

368
00:40:50,750 --> 00:40:55,246
- 被诅咒的食腐怪
- 不，这不可能
-Scavengers of the damned.
-No, no. lt's impossible.

369
00:40:55,421 --> 00:40:59,205
信不信由你
而且我认为它们不是来找我的
Yeah. And l don't think
they were after me.

370
00:41:01,344 --> 00:41:04,380
你真的认为她不是自杀的？
You really believe
she wouldn't commit suicide.

371
00:41:04,555 --> 00:41:05,966
伊莎贝尔？
lsabel?

372
00:41:06,766 --> 00:41:08,842
绝对不信
Never in a million years.

373
00:41:09,227 --> 00:41:11,303
好吧，我们来确认一下
Well, let's be sure.

374
00:41:11,521 --> 00:41:14,012
看看她是不是在地狱里
Let's see if she's in hell.

375
00:41:38,423 --> 00:41:40,664
哦，应该是冷水还是热水？
Oh, was it supposed to be hot or cold?

376
00:41:41,134 --> 00:41:43,292
放在椅子前面
ln front of the chair.

377
00:41:46,180 --> 00:41:48,007
真不敢相信我居然在干这个
l can't believe l'm doing this.

378
00:41:48,182 --> 00:41:50,804
- 这些都是伊莎贝尔的东西？
- 对
-These are all lsabel's things?
-Yeah.

379
00:41:52,020 --> 00:41:53,846
- 这猫呢？
- 达珂？
-How about the cat?
-Duck?

380
00:41:54,647 --> 00:41:56,640
是啊，怎么了？
Yeah, why?

381
00:41:57,692 --> 00:41:59,020
达珂
Duck.

382
00:41:59,193 --> 00:42:01,519
哦，觉得奇怪是么
Oh, you think that's strange.

383
00:42:01,696 --> 00:42:03,155
猫是很好的动物
Cats are good.

384
00:42:03,323 --> 00:42:04,947
很有灵性
Half in, half out anyway.

385
00:42:23,259 --> 00:42:26,462
如果你要施某种法术或什么的话
lf this is some kind of spell
or something. . .

386
00:42:26,638 --> 00:42:29,804
难道不需要点蜡烛和画五角星么？
. . .don't you need candles
and a pentagram for it to work?

387
00:42:29,974 --> 00:42:32,299
哦？你有吗？
Why, do you have any?

388
00:42:32,602 --> 00:42:35,556
- 简直是疯了
- 是的
-This is crazy.
-Yes.

389
00:42:39,067 --> 00:42:41,439
你得离开
l need you to leave.

390
00:42:42,278 --> 00:42:45,113
- 为什么？
- 安吉拉，拜托
-l'm sorry?
-Angela, please.

391
00:42:49,410 --> 00:42:51,403
我是说离开这屋子
The apartment.

392
00:42:53,414 --> 00:42:55,241
好吧
Okay.

393
00:43:01,589 --> 00:43:04,127
当心我的猫
Be careful with that cat.

394
00:43:08,262 --> 00:43:10,967
上帝，我恨干这个
God, l hate this part.

395
00:45:13,805 --> 00:45:16,592
- 伊莎贝尔
- 康斯坦丁
-lsabel.
-Constantine.

396
00:46:02,145 --> 00:46:03,555
安吉拉
Angela.

397
00:46:07,025 --> 00:46:08,567
上帝
Jesus.

398
00:46:12,780 --> 00:46:14,524
- 康斯坦丁，你怎么啦？
- 双胞胎
-Constantine, what--?
-Twins.

399
00:46:14,699 --> 00:46:16,608
上帝，你说什么？
Jesus. What?

400
00:46:17,535 --> 00:46:20,026
- 你们是双胞胎
- 你说什么？
-You were twins.
-What did you say?

401
00:46:20,204 --> 00:46:22,874
- 她是自杀的
- 什么？
-She killed herself.
-What?

402
00:46:24,000 --> 00:46:26,621
因此被罚入地狱
And she's damned for it.

403
00:46:39,599 --> 00:46:41,342
这怎么可能？
How is this possible?

404
00:46:43,895 --> 00:46:45,722
我得吃点东西
l need to eat.

405
00:48:33,546 --> 00:48:35,954
嗨，嗨！
你在这儿干什么？
Hey! Hey, what are you doing in here?

406
00:48:39,052 --> 00:48:40,878
别激动，哥们儿
Relax, man.

407
00:48:41,471 --> 00:48:43,297
慢点！
Slow down!

408
00:49:06,537 --> 00:49:09,455
这儿他妈的是什么地方？
What the hell kind of place is this?

409
00:50:00,049 --> 00:50:01,841
约翰
John.

410
00:50:32,290 --> 00:50:36,157
我小的时候
能看到一些东西
When l was a kid, l could see things.

411
00:50:36,669 --> 00:50:38,709
一些人类看不到的东西
Things humans aren't supposed to see.

412
00:50:40,298 --> 00:50:43,168
也是不应该看到的东西
Things you shouldn 't have to see.

413
00:51:00,777 --> 00:51:05,071
我父母都是正常人
他们像大多数父母一样
My parents were normal.
They did what most parents would do.

414
00:51:05,281 --> 00:51:07,737
让情况变得更糟
They made it worse.

415
00:51:10,203 --> 00:51:12,990
当你觉得再也无法忍受的时候
You think you're crazy long enough. . .

416
00:51:13,456 --> 00:51:14,784
你就会寻找出路
. . .you find a way out.

417
00:51:15,208 --> 00:51:19,040
- 你尝试自杀？
- 我什么都没尝试
-You tried to kill yourself.
-I didn 't try anything.

418
00:51:22,840 --> 00:51:25,925
准确的说，我死过两分钟
Officially, I was dead for two minutes.

419
00:51:26,803 --> 00:51:29,210
但是当我跨入另一个世界的时候
But when you cross over. . .

420
00:51:30,390 --> 00:51:32,715
时间就停止了
. . .time stops.

421
00:51:34,143 --> 00:51:37,014
我敢说
地狱里的两分钟就像一生那么漫长
Take it from me,
two minutes in hell is a lifetime.

422
00:51:38,940 --> 00:51:41,229
当我重回人世的时候
When l came back. . .

423
00:51:43,152 --> 00:51:44,944
我终于知道
. . .l knew. . .

424
00:51:45,279 --> 00:51:48,031
我能看到的所有的东西都是真实的
. . .all the things l could see were real.

425
00:51:49,367 --> 00:51:54,492
天堂和地狱无处不在
每一堵墙，每一扇窗后面
Heaven and hell are right here.
Behind every wall, every window.

426
00:51:54,664 --> 00:51:59,658
这个世界背后还有一个世界
而我们被夹在中间
The world behind the world,
and we're smack in the middle.

427
00:51:59,919 --> 00:52:03,370
天使和魔鬼都不能逾越
进入我们的世界
Angels and demons can't
cross over onto our plane.

428
00:52:03,548 --> 00:52:06,465
所以，我们看到的就是所谓的“杂种”
So instead we get
what l call half-breeds.

429
00:52:07,593 --> 00:52:09,835
蛊惑者
The influence peddlers.

430
00:52:10,013 --> 00:52:15,469
它们只能在你耳边煽风点火
但是它的一句话就能给你勇气
They can only whisper in our ears, but
a single word can give you courage...

431
00:52:15,643 --> 00:52:19,688
或者让你一下子从快乐的巅峰
掉落到痛苦的深渊
...or turn your favorite pleasure
into your worst nightmare.

432
00:52:19,856 --> 00:52:22,892
那些被魔鬼触碰的
Those with the demon 's touch...

433
00:52:23,067 --> 00:52:28,109
比如半天使
是和我们生活在一起的
...like those part angel,
living alongside us.

434
00:52:28,281 --> 00:52:30,772
他们称之为平衡
They call it the balance.

435
00:52:31,200 --> 00:52:34,320
而我称之为虚伪的狗屁
l call it hypocritical bullshit.

436
00:52:35,872 --> 00:52:38,445
所以当哪个杂种不守规矩
So when a half-breed breaks the rules. . .

437
00:52:38,958 --> 00:52:42,908
我会直接让他滚进地狱
. . .l deport their sorry ass
straight back to hell.

438
00:52:43,546 --> 00:52:46,167
这样的杂种太多了
l don't get them all. . .

439
00:52:47,342 --> 00:52:50,627
我只希望尽量多的除掉一些
让自己能够
. . .but l've been hoping to get enough
to ensure my. . .

440
00:52:51,638 --> 00:52:54,638
- 早点退休
- 我不懂
-. . .retirement.
-l don't understand.

441
00:52:56,601 --> 00:52:58,807
我就是在自杀，安吉拉
l'm a suicide, Angela.

442
00:52:58,978 --> 00:53:02,513
当我死的时候，按照规则
我只有一个地方可去
When l die, the rules say
l've got just one place to go.

443
00:53:02,690 --> 00:53:04,730
你是在积德，希望能进天堂
You're trying to buy your way
into heaven.

444
00:53:04,901 --> 00:53:07,439
要是你被关进一个
半数犯人都是你亲手抓进去的监狱里
What would you do
if you were sentenced to a prison. . .

445
00:53:07,612 --> 00:53:09,937
你会有什么感觉？
. . .where half the inmates
were put there by you?

446
00:53:12,325 --> 00:53:14,863
我想上帝为我们每个人都安排好了一切
l guess God has a plan for all of us.

447
00:53:15,286 --> 00:53:18,406
小姐
上帝只是一个玩蚂蚁的小孩
God's a kid with an ant farm, lady.

448
00:53:18,581 --> 00:53:20,621
他什么都没安排
He's not planning anything.

449
00:53:21,000 --> 00:53:22,993
在我们小的时候
When we were little. . .

450
00:53:24,003 --> 00:53:26,577
伊莎贝尔也能看到东西
. . .lsabel saw things too.

451
00:53:32,011 --> 00:53:33,422
道森
Dodson.

452
00:53:36,015 --> 00:53:39,515
警卫发现他在摸弄尸体
然后他仓皇跑到街对面
Guard spotted him groping the body,
then he ran across the street.

453
00:53:39,686 --> 00:53:42,770
跑进店里来
把货架上的酒打开喝了个遍
Came in here, and he had a go
at the entire stock.

454
00:53:42,939 --> 00:53:46,189
不到一分钟
他就溺死在酒里了
He drowned himself in alcohol
in under a minute.

455
00:53:46,776 --> 00:53:49,397
本可以成为我们教友会的一员的
Could've been a member
of my fraternity.

456
00:53:51,864 --> 00:53:53,822
他跑到这儿来干什么？
Hey, what the hell is he doing here?

457
00:53:54,117 --> 00:53:55,611
没关系
He's okay.

458
00:54:05,086 --> 00:54:08,704
为什么不给我打电话
狗娘养的
Why didn't you call me,
you son of a bitch?

459
00:54:43,458 --> 00:54:45,082
喂？
Yes?

460
00:54:46,210 --> 00:54:47,870
什么意思？
What do you mean?

461
00:54:48,796 --> 00:54:50,291
什么？
What?

462
00:54:50,465 --> 00:54:52,007
怎么会？
How?

463
00:55:03,519 --> 00:55:06,639
知道了，拜拜
Got it. Bye.

464
00:55:13,154 --> 00:55:16,155
我要看一下伊莎贝尔死亡的现场
l need to see where lsabel died.

465
00:55:16,324 --> 00:55:19,491
请神，占卜，通灵
Seances, Ouija boards, channeling.

466
00:55:20,119 --> 00:55:23,702
父亲以为她只是想引人注意
Our father thought she was
just trying to get attention.

467
00:55:23,956 --> 00:55:26,412
可事实上不是
She certainly did that.

468
00:55:26,626 --> 00:55:30,125
她把她看到的东西告诉每一个人
She'd tell everyone about the things
she said she saw.

469
00:55:30,296 --> 00:55:33,997
把母亲吓得半死
She'd scare my mother half to death.

470
00:55:35,802 --> 00:55:38,471
之后几乎一年
她始终一言不发
And then she stopped talking
for almost a year.

471
00:55:38,638 --> 00:55:40,880
所以你们把她送到这儿来了
So you had her committed.

472
00:55:41,057 --> 00:55:42,385
是的
Yeah.

473
00:55:42,558 --> 00:55:44,218
有多长时间了？
How long?

474
00:55:44,602 --> 00:55:46,310
两个星期
Two weeks.

475
00:55:46,813 --> 00:55:48,556
这一次
This time.

476
00:55:48,731 --> 00:55:53,310
她的病情时好时坏
最近又恶化了
She'd get better, and then she'd
get worse. Recently, a lot worse.

477
00:55:55,321 --> 00:55:58,939
那个死者手掌上刻的符号
That symbol that was cut
in the dead guy's hand. . .

478
00:55:59,117 --> 00:56:01,405
会不会和这有关？
. . .does it have something to do
with this?

479
00:56:01,744 --> 00:56:03,986
约翰，别忘了我是警察
l'm a cop, John, remember?

480
00:56:04,163 --> 00:56:09,121
一个人不可能什么都没留下
就这么跳楼自杀的
You don't walk off the roof of a building
without leaving something behind.

481
00:56:09,293 --> 00:56:14,169
而我已经把她所有的遗物都给你看过了
不过你尽管找
And l showed you everything
she left behind in that box, but feel free.

482
00:56:14,340 --> 00:56:19,679
也许她留下了一些
警察找不到的东西
Maybe she left something else.
Not something a cop would find.

483
00:56:21,180 --> 00:56:23,007
一些只有你才能找到的东西
Something just for you.

484
00:56:24,517 --> 00:56:28,729
你们是双胞胎，安吉拉
双胞胎的想法是相似的
You were her twin, Angela.
Twins tend to think alike.

485
00:56:28,896 --> 00:56:32,230
- 我不像我的妹妹
- 但你曾经是的
-l'm not like my sister.
-But you were once.

486
00:56:32,400 --> 00:56:34,606
当你们还是孩子的时候
When you were kids.

487
00:56:34,944 --> 00:56:37,696
当你们每时每刻形影不离的时候
When you'd spend every second
with each other.

488
00:56:37,864 --> 00:56:41,612
你说一句，她就能接下句
你受伤了，她就会哭
You'd start a sentence, she'd finish it.
You'd get hurt, she'd cry.

489
00:56:41,784 --> 00:56:43,243
那是很久以前了
That was a long time ago.

490
00:56:43,411 --> 00:56:45,368
那种联系不会这么轻易就消失的
That kind of bond doesn't
just disappear.

491
00:56:45,538 --> 00:56:47,614
这儿什么都没有
There is nothing here.

492
00:56:48,207 --> 00:56:51,374
- 得了吧
- 她在这间屋子里筹划了自己的死
-Hey. Come on.
-She planned her death in this room.

493
00:56:51,544 --> 00:56:54,960
她是在这儿想出来的
就在你所站的地方
She thought it up right here.
